import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    avg_count_per_hour = data.groupby('hour')['count'].mean()
    avg_count_per_hour.plot(kind='line')
    
    plt.xlabel('Hour')
    plt.ylabel('Average Count')
    plt.title('What is the average count of events per hour?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], errors='ignore')
    data = data.sort_values(by='time')
    
    plt.plot(data['time'], data['count'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.xlabel('Time')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.title('What is the overall trend of events over time?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
